{{DEFAULTSORT:Nukata clan}}
{{translated page|ja|額田部氏|version=96247839|comment=Imported full ja history}}

'''Nukatabe Clan''' (額田部氏) was an ancient Japanese {{ill|clan|ja|氏族|12=draft}}, originating from the {{ill|Nukatabe|ja|額田部|12=draft}} organization under the {{ill|Me|ja|名代|12=draft}} system.

== Overview ==
=== Ancestry ===
The Nukatabe Ren clan claimed descent from {{ill|Amatsuhikone|ja|天津彦根命|12=draft}} (referred to as Amatsuhikone no Mikoto in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}}). According to the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|12=draft}} (Left Capital, Kami Clan section), they were descendants of "Otowiigatsu no Mikoto" (意富伊我都命). This deity was one of those born from the {{ill|ukehi|ja|うけい|12=draft}} ritual between {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|12=draft}} and {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素戔嗚尊|12=draft}}, as described in {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}, Volume 1. Additionally, the clan is mentioned as an ancestor of the {{ill|Onokuchi no Miyatsuko|ja|凡河内氏|12=draft}} and {{ill|Yamashiro no Miyatsuko|ja|山背国造|12=draft}}.<ref>{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}, Kamiyo Volume 1, Sixth Section.</ref> The {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}} also associates the Nukatabe clan with the Nukatabe Yuzaka Ren and others listed in the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|12=draft}}.

A theory suggests the clan's establishment reflects conflicts between the Yamato and Izumo regions.{{See|{{ill|Nukatabe|ja|額田部|12=draft}}}}

=== Base of Operations ===
The clan's base was located in Nukata Village, {{ill|Heguri District|ja|平群郡|12=draft}}, Yamato Province (modern {{ill|Yamatokoriyama|ja|大和郡山市|12=draft}}), where they built their {{ill|ujidera|ja|氏寺|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kakuan-ji|ja|額安寺|12=draft}}. The preserved "Yamato Province Nukata-ji Temple Site and Strip Village Map" at the {{ill|National Museum of Japanese History|ja|国立歴史民俗博物館|12=draft}} provides a rare depiction of temple layouts and estates during the Nara period, revealing the clan’s faith and burial practices.

== Archaeological Evidence ==
=== Izumo Nukatabe Clan ===
The {{ill|Fudoki|ja|風土記|12=draft}} of {{ill|Izumo Province|ja|Izumo Province|12=draft}} mentions the Nukatabe no Omi family in its records on {{ill|Ōhara District|ja|大原郡|12=draft}}. One notable entry describes a previous {{ill|Shōryō|ja|少領|12=draft}}, Nukatabe no Omi Oshishima, who built a temple.<ref>{{ill|Izumo Fudoki|ja|Izumo Province 風土記|12=draft}}, Ōhara District, Tsūji Section.</ref>

A significant archaeological discovery related to this clan is the iron sword with silver-inlaid inscriptions found in the Okadayama Kofun (Matsue City, Shimane Prefecture). This sword, discovered during preservation work in 1983, bears the inscription "各田卩臣," interpreted as "Nukatabe no Omi." It suggests a connection to local governance during the late 6th century.

=== Other Artifacts ===
Other artifacts from the Okadayama Kofun include mirrors, weapons, and horse gear, reflecting the clan's social and political significance. These findings support the theory that Nukatabe no Omi managed local estates as part of the Yamato government’s administrative system.

== Key Figures ==
* '''Nukatabe Hirafu''' (額田部比羅夫): Notable as a diplomat under Empress Suiko, Hirafu welcomed the Sui envoy, Pei Shiqing, at Tsubaki Market and performed ceremonial duties.<ref>{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}, Empress Suiko, Year 16.</ref>
* '''Nukatabe no Omi Rei''' (額田部連甥): Appointed as {{ill|Hōtō|ja|法頭|12=draft}} during Emperor Kōtoku's reign (645 CE).<ref>{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}, Emperor Kōtoku, Year 1.</ref>

== Nukatabe Ren and Nukatabe Kawada Ren ==
The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|12=draft}} includes two origin stories:
* Nukatabe Yuzaka Ren received their surname after presenting a horse with a field-shaped marking to Emperor Ingyō.
* Nukatabe Kawada Ren also earned their name for offering a similarly marked horse.<ref>{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|12=draft}}, Emperor Ingyō Section.</ref>
== See Also ==
* {{ill|Be System|ja|部民制|12=draft}}

